{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_20","type":"reasoning","text":"**Identifying the Failure Stage**\n\nIt looks like the initial failure was with the Java runtime test setup. The method `LoggerFactory.getILoggerFactory()` stopped returning the Logback `LoggerContext` for version 1.5.30. The preserved branch has a fix that directly initializes `LogbackServiceProvider`, which is backed by log evidence. Earlier validations were successful, but since the automated job failed later, it seems the issue was during the iterative coverage and finalization stage. I should include both parts in my follow-up."}}
