{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_27","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed (`fails-java-run`, workflow status `failure`, reason `job_failed`), but preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1292-fails-java-run-ch.qos.logback-logback-classic-1.5.30-4ca5ae2b\n\nThe most likely failure was after the actual Java-run fix was generated, during the later coverage/finalization part of the workflow rather than in the underlying `logback-classic` fix itself. In `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T11-56-56-901056Z.log`, the preserved run identifies the concrete runtime issue for `1.5.30` (`LoggerFactory.getILoggerFactory()` returning SLF4J NOP instead of a Logback `LoggerContext` in this setup), updates the tests to initialize `LogbackServiceProvider` directly, and then reports both `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30 --stacktrace` and `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30 --stacktrace` as successful, with `76` tests successful. The preserved branch head also contains generated metadata and stats; `stats/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.30/stats.json` reports dynamic-access coverage at `17/17`, and the generated JVM test results under `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.30/build/test-results/test/` show zero failures, including `TEST-org.graalvm.logback.LogbackTests.xml` with `tests=\"76\" failures=\"0\" errors=\"0\"`.\n\nWhat appears to have gone wrong is that later iterative logs, especially `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T12-23-20-246059Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T12-26-15-863099Z.log`, add follow-up coverage commits but end with “Per instruction, I did not compile or run tests”, so the final preserved head was likely not revalidated before the workflow terminated. `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30/metadata-fix/codex.log` is also worth checking because it captures the earlier successful `./gradlew test` execution from the metadata-fix side.\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Check out the preserved branch and rerun `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30` and `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.30` on the branch head.\n2. If the branch head does not validate cleanly, compare it with the earlier validated state described in `pi-generation-2026-04-28T11-56-56-901056Z.log` and keep only the verified commits needed for `1.5.30`.\n3. If the preserved branch validates, use it as the basis for the manual follow-up PR or retrigger the workflow from that branch."}}
